parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Pressure Buildup and Leakage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The buildup of pressure in the fuel system can cause fuel to leak onto the ground, creating a fire hazard and increasing the risk of accidents.
The inability to adjust the rear view mirror outward can reduce the driver's visibility, increasing the risk of accidents or collisions, especially when changing lanes or merging with traffic.
symptoms: The rear view mirror is too close to the center
requiring the driver to lean to the opposite side to clear the field of view
obstructing the driver's ability to see behind the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden detachment of the side mirror can cause a distraction to the driver, increasing the risk of accidents or collisions, and may also obstruct the driver's view of the surrounding area.
symptoms: The side mirror comes off or detaches from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the inner weld on the inner pipes of the exhaust system can cause excessive noise and exhaust leaks, which can lead to decreased vehicle performance and potentially cause accidents due to distraction or decreased visibility.
symptoms: Loud rattling or hissing noise from the exhaust system

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil seat or ring can cause oil to leak onto the rims and tires, posing a significant risk of accidents due to loss of traction and control.
symptoms: Oil leaking onto the rims and tires

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the rear tire tread can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to surrounding components, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: potentially leading to vehicle instability or loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brakes to engage can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop, increasing the risk of accidents or collisions, especially when stopping on inclines or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The rear brakes do not engage when coming to a stop
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the rear brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the rear brake light does not illuminate.
